# README – Organization Category Flow Map

## Overview

This interactive page displays organizations on a map by location and category.

Each organization appears as a colored pin. Users can:

* View organizations geographically
* Click pins for details
* Search organizations by name
* Filter by category
* Zoom to all visible pins
* Collapse or expand the control panel

The page uses:

* Leaflet.js
* OpenStreetMap tiles
* Leaflet MarkerCluster

---

## How the Page Works

The file contains three main data sections:

1. Category colors (`CAT_COLORS`)
2. City coordinates (`CITY_LL`)
3. Organization dataset (`CSV`)

---

## 1. Category Colors

This section controls the color of pins.

```javascript
const CAT_COLORS = {
  'Democracy': '#2F6BFF',
  'Migration': '#FF5A7A'
};
```

The **Primary Category** determines the pin color.

---

## 2. City Coordinates

This section stores map coordinates.

```javascript
const CITY_LL = {
  'Berlin,Germany':[52.5200,13.4050],
  'Warsaw,Poland':[52.2370,21.0175]
};
```

Format:

```text
'City,Country':[Latitude,Longitude]
```

If a city is missing here, organizations in that city will not appear.

---

## 3. Organization Data

Organizations are stored in the CSV block.

```javascript
const CSV = `
Name of Organization;City;Country;Website;Primary Category;Secondary Category;Third Category
...`;
```

Each line = one organization.

---

# How to Add a New Organization

Add a new line inside the `CSV` section.

Format:

```text
Organization Name;City;Country;Website;Primary Category;Secondary Category;Third Category
```

Example:

```text
Example Organization;Berlin;Germany;https://example.org/;Democracy;Human/Fundamental rights;
```

---

## Column Meaning

| Column               | Meaning                        |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Name of Organization | Full organization name         |
| City                 | City name                      |
| Country              | Country name                   |
| Website              | Full website URL               |
| Primary Category     | Main category (controls color) |
| Secondary Category   | Optional                       |
| Third Category       | Optional                       |

---

## Important Rules

### Rule 1: City Must Exist in `CITY_LL`

If the city is new, first add coordinates.

Example:

```javascript
'Lisbon,Portugal':[38.7223,-9.1393],
```

Then add the organization row:

```text
Open Europe Lisbon;Lisbon;Portugal;https://example.pt/;Democracy;;
```

---

### Rule 2: Use Existing Category Names

Use only these values:

* Democracy
* Human/Fundamental rights
* International/intercultural Understanding
* Energy/Climate/Sustainability
* Trade/Economy
* Migration
* Conflict/War
* Digital Technology
* Digital Media
* European Integration
* other

---

### Rule 3: Primary Category Controls Color

Example:

```text
Example NGO;Berlin;Germany;https://example.org/;Migration;Democracy;
```

This organization will use the Migration color.

---

## Search Function

Typing in the search box filters by organization name.

Example:

```text
Amnesty
```

Shows organizations with “Amnesty” in their name.

---

## Category Filtering

Checkboxes filter visible organizations.

If an organization belongs to multiple categories, selecting any of them will show it.

---

## Common Problems

### Organization Does Not Appear

Usually caused by missing city coordinates.

Check `CITY_LL`.

### Wrong Pin Color

Category name is misspelled.

Use the approved category names.

### Website Not Clickable

Use full URLs:

```text
https://example.org
```

---

